    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Tough, honest driver with solid bones and plenty of upside. Starts, runs, and moves under its own power, with an engine that pulls cleanly and a drivetrain that feels like it still has life left in it. This is the kind of car that rewards someone who knows their way around maintenance and wants a capable budget platform rather than a trailer queen. Cosmetically it shows age and needs attention, but the core mechanical package makes it a strong candidate for a workhorse, weekend project, or inexpensive entry point. If you want something affordable with usable performance character and room to improve, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 7850.0,
